<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-08-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-08-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1337" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1337">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/15719.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Consul <persName type="to">Letcher</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 12, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>General Scott telegraphs from El Paso General Villa has given assurances
                            properties of foreign merchants in Chihuahua will be returned to them
                            but that they will be prosecuted in the civil court for any infraction
                            of the law; also that no meeting of mining men will be held at
                            Chihuahua.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>